PITTSBURGH Two annual
memorial awards honoring
former football players Willie
Calimore and John Harrington,
were announced by the Pitts
burgh Courier and Royal Crown
Cola, Co., Columbus, Ga.


Galimore and Harrington, both
members of the National League
champions Chicago Bears in
1868, were killed in an auto
accident during training sea son
in Indiana.


harrington was a graduate of
Prairie View A&M College and
Galimore led his team to honors
at Florida A&M University.


The harrington awards will
be presented to the two outstand-
ing rockies in the National and
America football leagues who
played at predominantly Negro
colleges. The galimore awards
will be given to two out standing
league players who competed at
Negro colleges.


The wards banquet will be held
in December.

Many Elk brothers and daugh-
tiers turned out to honor Bro. Ben
ME Nicholson on his o5th birth
day. AS he blew out his candle
he wished to be around on the
Tooth.


His surprise gift, a car coat
was greatly appreciated. We
should never forget our aged or
invalided members.


We are expecting big crowd
at our annual Spookeroo Halo
ween Dance, Oct. 81. 1t Is the
annual must affair sponsored by
the Grand Canyon Temple. Dona-
ton $l.25.

Ruby Blackshear, 1907 S. l 9th
Drive; DIT. Katherine Ba IS, 1901
w. Cocopah, and DIT. Lillian Flora
Hightower, 9O4 S. 9TH Ave.

Join us and have fun.


Watch for the November full

Charlesetta McClammy
